{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, CNNs excel in efficient spatial feature extraction, rendering them suitable for HAR tasks with fixed-size sensor inputs.",
    "However, their limitations in handling long temporal dependencies may require meticulous design and segmentation strategies.",
    "RNNs, particularly LSTMs, balance sequential modeling and computational efficiency, but their performance may still be influenced by sequence length and model complexity.",
    "Ensemble models, while offering a potential solution to prior challenges, come at the expense of increased inference time as at least two models are run for the same classification task.",
    "Transfer Learning, although promising, can face obstacles due to domain dissimilarity, necessitating task-specific fine-tuning."
  ]
}